text: They won't remember any of this but I'll carry the humiliation that swelled inside me today for years to come. It made every insecurity I had from 6th to 12th, that I had been able to leave behind or confront, come alive. It was bullying and I know I'll never meet you all again.

Today awoke some of the most awful fears I've had about my self image. About the beard that barely grows, the tone of my voice, the difficulty I have in focusing fully on a conversation, the excitement I have in a social atmosphere. I know I don't deserve this and yet I feel I do

We are all fucking adults. Grow the fuck up. There are ways to needle a friend like in the "good old days" that isn't subtle mockery of everything from physical features to what they post on Instagram to mockingly laugh at everything I didn't know or misheard.

No you assholes, I'm not interested in being your butt of jokes anymore, nothing you do makes you cool, you have zero empathy for people who aren't your "close friends" and your "laundon wali baat" is an excuse for you to relive the actually awful folks you were.

Some people remind you of the very reason you chose to cut off from about everybody in your past. What was supposed to be catching up with "friends" today after a decade became a nightmare where I doubted and hated almost everything about myself rather than hating them.

Someone came all the way to a far off metro station to drop their partner. The deep hug and subtle kisses between both as the guy went back.....visually it felt like love in its purest form
Well, almost. There's a new, albeit vastly reduced, infection in the news and there's this mystery flu all of Delhi is getting hit with. I'm wearing a mask outside as I type this. How oddly fitting.

I can't believe I write this 3 years later in a new normal. I never met my colleagues ever again because all of us left that job in less than a year. All of us who made it just look forward to the usual. The word "new" in the new normal has faded.

And you'd pray each day that your first notification of the day wasn't WhatsApp telling you that your friend lost their loved one, or worse, you yourself, despite somehow managing to pull a bed and an oxygen cylinder together.

And then before you knew COVID was raging and you were fervently praying your loved ones don't get it and if they did, they survive somehow. I was remotely volunteering to help friends find beds and equipment in Delhi, call after call in manic desperation.

It took another 3 months to get my belongings out, my lovely manager going out of all way to get it done. Groceries were limited, disaster in managing your hairdo kept happening, but barring the heightened fear each time we had to get groceries, staying home was smooth.

If not for the ridiculous foresight (or wherever they got the right info from) by my parents, I'd have been in a claustrophobic 1 RK studio flat in the nether region of Gurgaon where even the network sucked, and let's just say a recent conflict had me very scared of my neighbour.
That day, 18 March 2020, was a Wednesday. The news just got scarier as that week closed, and culminated with the "janata curfew" on Sunday. And after that day and week....life was never the same.

4:00 AM, still very much in that state, I get a cab to office and after some interrogation the guards accompany me to my cubicle to retrieve it. I make it to the airport, and end up home sleepy at 7 am. My mom was like "just 1 week's clothes?" cuz I was still skeptical.

The firmness and alarm surprised me - how were they so sure? But I agree & they buy me a one way for the first flight next morn.
At 2 am, in what I'd call a "very sensory" state, God knows how I manage to pack a week's worth of clothes to realise my laptop charger is missing

We ended up at my manager's flat to have fun - a lot of fun. All concern tossed aside. I call and tell my parents about the temporary WFH.
Their response is firm - come home tomorrow immediately. This is *not* going to be temporary at all. Like it or not, we're buying you tix

God knows what happened around 3-4 pm because we were gathered and told a "trial WFH" was being implemented that Thurs-Sun to "test out" remote working, and told to report to work next Monday. Some of us had this feeling this wasn't going to be temporary at all.

Well, everywhere except my then workplace. Initially concern was dismissed by the founder (not the wisest choice considering their immunocompromised partner literally being our colleague). We were getting worried at the lack of any mandate.

17 March 2020. There was one thing on everybody's minds - this new virus originating from China that was starting to hit our shores. People were preparing in light of absent govt communication - offices declaring precautionary WFH, communities creating Discord groups, masks.....
